{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896783365,"sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb26362001B5dmf72mudryFe","messageID":"msg_d7bb248ab0013lr3AzLEwZ1RlU","sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md","offset":1143},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1143:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n1144:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n1145:         self.stderr = stderr\n1146:         self.command = command\n1147:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n1148: \n1149: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n1150:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n1151:     pass\n1152: \n1153: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n1154:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n1155:     pass\n1156: ```\n1157: \n1158: ## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n1159: \n1160: ```toml\n1161: dependencies = [\n1162:     \"requests\",\n1163:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n1164:     \"cryptography\",\n1165: ]\n1166: ```\n1167: \n1168: - `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n1169: - Build: `setuptools>=61.0`, `wheel`; backend `setuptools.build_meta`\n1170: - Packages: `where = [\".\"]`, `include = [\"agentcube*\"]`, `namespaces = false`\n1171: \n1172: \n1173: --- python-sdk/spec.md ---\n1174: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n1175: \n1176: ## Purpose\n1177: \n1178: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n1179: \n1180: ## Requirements\n1181: \n1182: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n1183: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n1184: \n1185: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n1186: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n1187: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n1188: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n1189: \n1190: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n1191: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n1192: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n1193: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n1194: \n1195: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n1196: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n1197: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n1198: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n1199: \n1200: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n1201: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n1202: \n1203: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n1204: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n1205: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n1206: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n1207: \n1208: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n1209: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n1210: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n1211: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n1212: \n1213: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n1214: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n1215: \n1216: #### Scenario: Context manager\n1217: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n1218: - **WHEN** the block exits\n1219: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n1220: \n1221: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n1222: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n1223: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n1224: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n1225: \n1226: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n1227: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n1228: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n1229: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n1230: \n1231: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n1232: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n1233: \n1234: #### Scenario: Create session\n1235: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n1236: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n1237: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n1238: \n1239: #### Scenario: Delete session\n1240: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n1241: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n1242: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n1243: \n1244: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n1245: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n1246: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n1247: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n1248: \n1249: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n1250: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n1251: \n1252: #### Scenario: Execute command\n1253: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n1254: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n1255: \n1256: #### Scenario: Files API\n1257: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n1258: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n1259: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n1260: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n1261: \n1262: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n1263: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n1264: \n1265: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n1266: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n1267: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n1268: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n1269: \n1270: ### Requirement: Session header management\n1271: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n1272: \n1273: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n1274: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n1275: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n1276: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n1277: \n1278: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n1279: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n1280: \n1281: #### Scenario: Command failure\n1282: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n1283: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n1284: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n1285: \n1286: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n1287: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n1288: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n1289: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n1290: \n1291: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n1292: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n1293: \n1294: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n1295: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n1296: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n1297: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n1298: \n1299: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n1300: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n1301: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n1302: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n1303: \n1304: ---\n1305: \n1306: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n1307: \n1308: \n1309: Use OpenSpec format. Each requirement must have acceptance scenarios.\n\n(End of file - total 1309 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n## Dependencies (`sdk-python/pyproject.toml`)\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md","time":{"start":1775896783342,"end":1775896783362}}}}
