{"type":"text","timestamp":1775896794569,"sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb290cf001rQeeCK4PhUdmz2","messageID":"msg_d7bb26a44001EeJbSSEBdDT46L","sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the task. I need to write a `delta-spec.md` file for AR-025 (MetadataService and Data Models) in the agentcube project. Let me create this file with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios based on the base specs provided.","time":{"start":1775896794567,"end":1775896794567}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775896883348,"sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb3513d001diwB29VCMVrZi8","messageID":"msg_d7bb26a44001EeJbSSEBdDT46L","sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","type":"text","text":" files","time":{"start":1775896883344,"end":1775896883344}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896883360,"sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb295ca001XCD2wF5xPfXWQR","messageID":"msg_d7bb26a44001EeJbSSEBdDT46L","sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:2","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-025: MetadataService 与数据模型 — Delta Specification\n\n## Module\n`cmd/cli` — AgentCube CLI Toolkit\n\n## Language\nPython\n\n## Overview\nThis delta spec extends the base cli-toolkit specification with detailed acceptance scenarios for `MetadataService` and the data models (`AgentMetadata`, `MetadataOptions`). These components form the core configuration management layer for agent lifecycle operations.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: MetadataService — Load and Save Operations\nThe system SHALL provide `MetadataService` to load and persist `AgentMetadata` from/to YAML files, with fallback filenames and validation.\n\n#### Scenario: Load metadata from primary filename\n- **GIVEN** a workspace containing `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be read and parsed into an `AgentMetadata` instance\n\n#### Scenario: Load metadata with fallback chain\n- **GIVEN** a workspace without `agent_metadata.yaml` but with `agent.yaml`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml` if the previous is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Load metadata file not found\n- **GIVEN** a workspace without any metadata file (`agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` with a message indicating no metadata file was found\n\n#### Scenario: Save metadata to canonical location\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` instance\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` is called\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace_path}/agent_metadata.yaml` with YAML format, `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, and `exclude_none=True`\n\n#### Scenario: Update metadata with partial dict\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and a dict of updates\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL load existing metadata, apply updates, save the merged result, and return the updated `AgentMetadata`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: AgentMetadata — Pydantic Model Validation\nThe system SHALL define `AgentMetadata` as a Pydantic `BaseModel` with comprehensive fields and validators for agent configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Required fields validation\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name` is missing\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating `agent_name` is required\n\n#### Scenario: Language validation\n- **GIVEN** `language` is set to `\"ruby\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` with message indicating language must be one of `['python', 'java']`\n\n#### Scenario: Language lowercase normalization\n- **GIVEN** `language` is `\"PYTHON\"` or `\"Python\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** the validator SHALL normalize it to `\"python\"` (lowercase)\n\n#### Scenario: Build mode validation\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is set to `\"hybrid\"`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` with message indicating build_mode must be one of `['local', 'cloud']`\n\n#### Scenario: Port range validation\n- **GIVEN** `port` is set to `0` or `70000`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` with message indicating port must be between 1 and 65535\n\n#### Scenario: Valid port values\n- **GIVEN** `port` is `8080`, `80`, or `443`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** the model SHALL be created successfully\n\n#### Scenario: Default values applied\n- **GIVEN** only `agent_name` and `entrypoint` are provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`, `requirements_file=\"requirements.txt\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Optional fields as None\n- **GIVEN** optional fields (`description`, `version`, `image`, `auth`, etc.) are not provided\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** these fields SHALL default to `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Image info structure\n- **GIVEN** `image` is a dict with keys like `name`, `tag`, `url`\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** the `image` field SHALL accept the `Dict[str, Any]` structure\n\n#### Scenario: Auth configuration structure\n- **GIVEN** `auth` is a dict with authentication settings\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** the `auth` field SHALL accept the `Dict[str, Any]` structure\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment info structure\n- **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment` is a dict with deployment metadata\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` is instantiated\n- **THEN** the `k8s_deployment` field SHALL accept the `Dict[str, Any]` structure\n\n#### Scenario: Serialize to dict with exclusions\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` instance with some `None` fields\n- **WHEN** `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` is called\n- **THEN** the resulting dict SHALL exclude all fields with `None` values\n\n#### Scenario: Serialize to JSON\n- **GIVEN** an `AgentMetadata` instance\n- **WHEN** `model_dump_json()` is called\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be a valid JSON string representing the metadata\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: MetadataOptions — CLI Options Dataclass\nThe system SHALL define `MetadataOptions` as a dataclass to capture CLI option overrides for the `pack` command.\n\n#### Scenario: From options dict conversion\n- **GIVEN** a dict with CLI options like `{\"agent_name\": \"my-agent\", \"language\": \"python\"}`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `MetadataOptions` instance with corresponding fields set\n\n#### Scenario: Default values in MetadataOptions\n- **GIVEN** an empty dict is passed to `from_options`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options({})` is called\n- **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `language=\"python\"`, `port=8080`, `build_mode=\"local\"`, `readiness_probe_port=8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Registry configuration defaults\n- **GIVEN** no registry options are provided\n- **WHEN** `MetadataOptions` is created\n- **THEN** registry fields SHALL default to empty string `''`: `registry_url`, `registry_username`, `registry_password`\n\n#### Scenario: Optional fields handling\n- **GIVEN** `agent_name`, `entrypoint`, `description`, `requirements_file` are not provided\n- **WHEN** `MetadataOptions` is created\n- **THEN** these fields SHALL be `None`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload manager and router URLs\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `router_url` are provided\n- **WHEN** `MetadataOptions` is created\n- **THEN** these fields SHALL store the URL strings\n\n#### Scenario: Readiness probe configuration\n- **GIVEN** `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port` are provided\n- **WHEN** `MetadataOptions` is created\n- **THEN** these fields SHALL be stored for AgentRuntime CR deployment\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: MetadataService — Workspace Validation\nThe system SHALL validate workspace structure based on the configured language.\n\n#### Scenario: Validate workspace exists\n- **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Python workspace success\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"` and workspace contains at least one `*.py` file\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Python workspace failure\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"` and workspace contains no `*.py` files\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Java workspace success\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"` and workspace contains `pom.xml`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Validate Java workspace failure\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"` and workspace lacks `pom.xml`\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating `pom.xml` is required for Java projects\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: MetadataService — Integration with PackRuntime\nThe system SHALL integrate `MetadataService` with `PackRuntime` for metadata loading and creation during the pack operation.\n\n#### Scenario: Load existing metadata during pack\n- **GIVEN** a workspace with existing `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `MetadataService.load_metadata` to read existing configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Create new metadata during pack\n- **GIVEN** a workspace without existing metadata file\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called with options\n- **THEN** it SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` instance using options and inferred values\n\n#### Scenario: Apply CLI option overrides\n- **GIVEN** existing metadata and CLI options dict\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL update metadata fields with non-None values from options, using `MetadataOptions.from_options`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Metadata File Format and Schema\nThe system SHALL persist metadata as YAML with specific formatting rules and schema version.\n\n#### Scenario: YAML format conventions\n- **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n- **WHEN** the YAML file is written\n- **THEN** it SHALL use block style (not flow style), 2-space indentation, and preserve key order\n\n#### Scenario: Schema validation on load\n- **GIVEN** a YAML file with invalid field types (e.g., `port: \"not-a-number\"`)\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` parses it\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` during `AgentMetadata` construction\n\n#### Scenario: Unknown field handling\n- **GIVEN** a YAML file with extra fields not in `AgentMetadata` schema\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` parses it\n- **THEN** Pydantic by default SHALL ignore/exclude extra fields (or raise if configured with `extra='forbid'`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: MetadataService — Error Handling\nThe system SHALL provide consistent error handling for metadata operations.\n\n#### Scenario: YAML parsing error\n- **GIVEN** a corrupted or invalid YAML file\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` attempts to parse it\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `yaml.YAMLError` or wrap it in a descriptive exception\n\n#### Scenario: Permission denied on save\n- **GIVEN** the workspace is read-only\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `PermissionError` with context about the failed write\n\n#### Scenario: Directory path instead of file\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists as a directory, not a file\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL handle the `IsADirectoryError` gracefully with a descriptive message\n\n---\n\n## Data Model Reference\n\n### AgentMetadata Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Default | Validation |\n|-------|------|----------|---------|------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Yes | — | Non-empty string |\n| `entrypoint` | `str` | Yes | — | Non-empty string |\n| `language` | `str` | No | `\"python\"` | Enum: `['python', 'java']`, lowercase |\n| `port` | `int` | No | `8080` | Range: `1-65535` |\n| `build_mode` | `str` | No | `\"local\"` | Enum: `['local', 'cloud']`, lowercase |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | Any string or None |\n| `version` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | Semantic version string |\n| `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | No | `None` | Image info dict |\n| `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | No | `None` | Auth config dict |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | No | `\"requirements.txt\"` | File path string |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | No | `\"\"` | URL string |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | No | `\"\"` | Username string |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | No | `\"\"` | Password string |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | URL string |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | URL string |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | URL string |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | Path string |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | No | `None` | Port number |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | Agent identifier |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | Session identifier |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | No | `None` | Deployment info dict |\n| `region` | `Optional[str]` | No | `None` | Region string |\n\n### MetadataOptions Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Default |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `language` | `Optional[str]` | `\"python\"` |\n| `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n| `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `\"local\"` |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n\n---\n\n## Files Affected\n\n- `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` — `MetadataService` class\n- `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` — `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n- `agentcube/services/__init__.py` — Services package exports\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` — `BaseModel` for `AgentMetadata`\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` — YAML parsing and serialization\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775896883351,"end":1775896883357}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775896883386,"sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb3f09f001jx3JgBuelTPV1d","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7bb26a44001EeJbSSEBdDT46L","sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":36971,"input":4,"output":4006,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":2879,"read":30082}},"cost":0}}
