{"type":"text","timestamp":1775897074932,"sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","part":{"id":"prt_d7bb6b455001roC6sYogF6L1GR","messageID":"msg_d7bb664de0019sMBLCST4DeLR6","sessionID":"ses_2844dc73affeS3a2G56QmO63kk","type":"text","text":"I've successfully written the `delta-spec.md` file for AR-025 (MetadataService and Data Models). The specification includes comprehensive GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios covering:\n\n## Summary of Coverage\n\n**MetadataService Operations (16 scenarios):**\n- Load with fallback chain (`agent_metadata.yaml` → `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`)\n- Save with proper YAML formatting\n- Update with partial dicts\n- Workspace validation for Python and Java projects\n\n**AgentMetadata Validation (21 scenarios):**\n- Required fields (`agent_name`, `entrypoint`)\n- Language validation and normalization (python/java, lowercase)\n- Build mode validation (local/cloud, lowercase)\n- Port range validation (1-65535)\n- Optional fields with defaults\n- Serialization (dict/JSON with `exclude_none`)\n\n**MetadataOptions Dataclass (8 scenarios):**\n- Default values\n- `from_options()` factory method\n- Partial field initialization\n\n**YAML & Error Handling (10 scenarios):**\n- Schema validation\n- Invalid YAML handling\n- Permission errors\n- File/directory edge cases\n\n**Integration (6 scenarios):**\n- PackRuntime integration\n- Metadata lifecycle during pack operations\n\nThe file also includes:\n- **Data Model Reference Tables** for `AgentMetadata` and `MetadataOptions` fields\n- **File Index** showing affected files\n- **Dependencies** (pydantic>=2.0.0, pyyaml>=6.0)\n- **API Reference** with class signatures\n- **Integration Points** showing how MetadataService connects to other components\n- **Implementation Notes** with best practices","time":{"start":1775897074930,"end":1775897074930}}}
